A coroutine function that returns a unique key\n\n  : to identify the user agent.\n\n  limits: Optional list of limits to use. Use instead of limit\n\n  : & period,\n\n```python\nasync def example_key_function() -> str:\n    return request.remote_addr\n```\n"]}, {"name": "quart_rate_limiter.rate_exempt", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["A decorator to mark the route as exempt from rate limits.\n\nThis should be used to wrap a route handler (or view function) to\nensure no rate limits are applied to the route. Note that it is\nimportant that this decorator be wrapped by the route decorator\nand not vice, versa, as below.\n\n```python\n@app.route('/')\n@rate_exempt\nasync def index():\n    ...\n```\n"]}, {"name": "quart_rate_limiter.limit_blueprint", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "blueprint", "type": {"name": "U", "xref": {"fqname": "U", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "limit", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "period", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "timedelta", "xref": {"fqname": "datetime.timedelta", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "key_function", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "KeyCallable", "xref": {"fqname": "KeyCallable", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "skip_function", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "SkipCallable", "xref": {"fqname": "SkipCallable", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "limits", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "RateLimit", "xref": {"fqname": "quart_rate_limiter.RateLimit", "project": null}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "U", "xref": {"fqname": "U", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["A function to add a rate limit marker to the blueprint.\n\nThis should be used to apply a rate limit to all routes registered\non the blueprint.\n\n```python\nblueprint = Blueprint(\"name\", __name__)\nlimit_blueprint(blueprint, 10, timedelta(seconds=10))\n```\n\nArguments:\n\n: blueprint: The blueprint to limit.\n  limit: The maximum number of requests to serve within a\n\n  > period.\n\n  period: The duration over which the number of requests must\n\n  : not exceed the *limit*.\n\n  key_function: A coroutine function that returns a unique key\n\n  : to identify the user agent.\n\n  limits: Optional list of limits to use. Use instead of limit\n\n  : & period,\n\n```python\nasync def example_key_function() -> str:\n    return request.remote_addr\n```\n"]}, {"name": "quart_rate_limiter.remote_addr_key", "asynchronous": true, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "quart_rate_limiter.QUART_RATE_LIMITER_LIMITS_ATTRIBUTE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "quart_rate_limiter.QUART_RATE_LIMITER_EXEMPT_ATTRIBUTE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "quart_rate_limiter.KeyCallable", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "quart_rate_limiter.SkipCallable", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "quart_rate_limiter.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "quart_rate_limiter.U", "type": n